
// The provided Hyperlambda code uses the [sockets.signal] slot to send a message to a specific session. It constructs the message using the [strings.concat] slot, which concatenates strings, and sends it with a type of "system" as part of the [args] node. This allows for real-time communication with connected clients in a specified session.
sockets.signal:x:@.reference/*/session
   args
      message:x:@strings.concat
      type:system
